{
  "stem": "8786.3",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] They were ready to go into a hospital and put everything on fire.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You had hundreds of people, children or women, doesn't matter.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It didn't mean nothing.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "As long as they know that they were Jewish, they were taking out people.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Doctors, they took out 30-- 300 doctors they took out into the Danube and they were just killing them.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The water of the Danube was red for days, people were saying.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "My own brother was in Budapest and he witnessed this abnormal brutality what this Szalasi and his gangsters committed.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Anyway, we were out in-- in Ruthenia, marching back to Hungary.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And we didn't know about what Szalasi was doing in Budapest, but the war continued.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "We knew that it wasn't what we-- we expected to be.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And we were marching back from-- from the border all the way, little by little by little, up to the Miskolc through [NON-ENGLISH], which was a well known town in Hungary.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "On the roads, they were full of beautiful-- it was in the time of the year when they had beautiful grapes and all the fruit, fruit orchards were full.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And there was-- we were not hungry there.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "We had plenty to eat in these Hungarian towns.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And we spoke their language.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "It was a different game than outside.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Sure enough, we were coming in to the Miskolc area.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "We stayed there for about two weeks in that place.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] But Hungary was little by little occupied by the Germans-- by the Russians.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And all those labor camps or forced laborers, the Germans and the Hungarian government did not want us to fall into the hands of the Russians, because that would mean liberation for us.",
      "word_count": 33
    }
  ],
